To build QNX image:
  Install BSP (Board Support Package) for PPC BE (big endian)
    The package can be found in
        //ventura/shared/dechen/palmbeach/qnx_atlantis_disco2_bsp.
  Make sure you have the working license file
    To update, copy the new license file to c:\QNXsdk
    Then on the window command prompt, do:
        set LM_LICENSE_FILE=c:\QNXsdk\<license_file>
        run c:\QNXsdk\host\win32\x86\usr\qnxlm\lmgrd -z
    Make sure the lmgrd process is not already running,
    otherwise kill it in task manager.
  After BSP installation:
    cd c:\QNXsdk\target\qnx6\usr\src\bsp-6.2.0\ppc\atlantis
    do a make to create the build file.
    cd image
    modify the build file
    do a make to build the QNX image file


To download QNX image:
  copy QNX image to /auto/tftpboot/<userid>
  telnet to eval board (using eval_con alias) set up in the lab
  set up following environment variables:
      TFTP_VERBOSE=2
      TFTP_CHECKSUM=0
      IP_SUBNET_MASK=255.255.0.0
      TFTP_SERVER=223.255.254.254
      DEFAULT_GATEWAY=1.11.0.1
      IP_ADDRESS= <board specific>
      MAC_ADDRESS= <board specific>
      TFTP_FILE= <filename>
  do a tftpdnld
  <QNX session>
  To quit QNX, type exit.
  To quit telnet session, press ctrl-], then type quit.


